    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-01-02T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-01-02T14:00:00-05:00" n="343"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d343">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.2383/1–249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d343fn1">This telegram was repeated to Tel Aviv for
                        information.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-01-02T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 2, 1949—2 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                    </gloss>
                </p>
                <p>7. Dept this morning requested Brit Emb inform <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                        >FonOff</gloss> that in view <gloss target="#t_PGI1">PGI</gloss> order
                    withdraw all Israeli forces from Egyptian territory as result our
                    representations and in view info contained Tel Aviv’s unnumbered tel Jan 1, 11
                    a. m.<note n="2" xml:id="d343fn2">See telegram 2 and footnote 1, <hi
                            rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> (being repeated London) Dept strongly
                    believes Brit should impress on Egyptians necessity their refraining from
                    further attacks similar that on Tel Aviv. Otherwise chain of reprisals set off
                    may well jeopardize progress toward final settlement so far made.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
